## Task Completion:

**1. Analyze and Describe the Main Target Image:**

- **Count & Layers:** The structure is composed of 13 blocks and has a maximum of 4 layers in the train part and 3 layers in the house part.
- **Spatial Relationships:**
    - **Layer 1 (Bottom):** Two orange cylinder blocks are placed horizontally side-by-side on the left. To their right, two red arch blocks are positioned next to each other, forming an archway.
    - **Layer 2:** A green rectangular block is placed horizontally atop the two orange cylinders. Another green rectangular block is placed horizontally spanning across the two red arch blocks. A blue cube is placed on top of the left red arch block. A yellow semi-cylinder block is placed on top of the right red arch block.
    - **Layer 3:** Two blue cubes are stacked vertically on top of the green rectangular block over the cylinders. A red roof block is placed on top of the blue cube on the left arch. A yellow rectangular block is placed vertically on top of the yellow semi-cylinder. An orange roof block is placed on top of the green rectangular block over the arches.
    - **Layer 4 (Top):** The second blue cube of the train stack forms the top layer of the train section.

**2. Select the Required Blocks from the Dictionary:**

- **Needed Blocks and Indices:**
    - Orange Cylinder (horizontal): Block 10 (used twice)
    - Green Rectangle (horizontal): Block 6 (used twice)
    - Blue Cube: Block 3 (used three times)
    - Red Arch: Block 1 (used twice)
    - Yellow Semi-cylinder: Block 11
    - Red Roof: Block 15
    - Yellow Rectangle (vertical): Block 9
    - Orange Roof: Block 16

- **List of Block Indices:** 10, 10, 6, 3, 3, 3, 1, 1, 6, 11, 15, 9, 16
